name: The Planets - No. 1, Mars (The Bringer of War)
The Planets - No. 2, Venus (The Bringer of Peace)
The Planets - No. 3, Mercury (the Winged Messenger)
comments: In an early sketch for the "The Planets" suite Holst listed Mercury as "no. 1", which musicologist Richard Greene suggests raises the possibility that the composer's first idea was simply to depict the planets in the obvious order, from nearest the sun to the farthest. "However, opening with the more disturbing character of Mars allows a more dramatic and compelling working out of the musical material".
